{"timestamp":"2026-06-03T07:35:30.425Z","type":"mistake","lesson":"DON'T: When adding a new method to a shared supabase query-builder chain (e.g. card_artifacts._fetch_research gaining .is_(\"workstream_id\",\"null\")), I only updated/ran ONE of the test files that mock that chain (test_card_artifacts_precedence.py) and missed the second (test_me_signals_pagination.py), which lacked an is_() method on its mock — green locally but CI's full suite went red. Lesson: when you change a query chain used in multiple modules, grep for ALL test files mocking that table/chain and run the FULL backend suite (pytest -q), not a single file, before pushing.","severity":"medium","files":["backend/app/card_artifacts.py","backend/tests/test_card_artifacts_precedence.py","backend/tests/test_me_signals_pagination.py"]}
